venue.name: Ser Seng Herbs (Turtle) Restaurant 生成山瑞補品

tips.text: Been a regular for years and I go here solely for black chicken herbal soup, not anything turtle-ish. The flavor of the soup has been consistently good and I pair it with a bowl of yam rice. YUM!
The porridge and macaroni is very nice. The ngoh hiang is one of the best.
Peanut dumpling soya bean is nice!

venue.name: River South (Hoe Nam) Prawn Noodles 河南肉骨大蝦面

tips.text: Go before 3pm for the real deal. After 3pm, the stall will be taken over by another relative whose skills are very average.
Food was great. Environment is good. Bubble loves it! Good job!
new INDIAN FOOD shop... a bit expensive.
tiramisu is a MUST TRY.  apple crumble was not bad. a mix of the warm and cold.

formattedAddress: Lao Zhong Zhong Eating House (29 Tai Thong Crescent)

tips.text: Pork & liver porridge with egg ...makes a yummy supper.
Creamy buttery crab is a MUST try!
Breakfast deluxe for the one's with big appetites

venue.name: 姑媽家 Gu Ma Jia Food Pot

tips.text: Sambal chilli sucks, Wu Xiang sucks... Basically only the Assam fish head can try
Aku pernah keini sama mamma pappa budhe pakdhe dan mba aya
There's this auntie with long hair tied with a pink/red rubber band working at the drinks stall her attutide sucks to the core!!! So damn rude!!! >:[ don't order drinks from her.
Food tastes good but expensive for the place! They have many people to serve but have to make order in the counter and use cash machine to pay.
4 bucks is quite pricy.. And the noodles is so-so only. Verdict is B

tips.text: Curry puff is a must try!!
I am the Mayor here.

Since the time I tried the XO fish head soup here, I have not come across anywhere else better.
Gd place for breakfast and lunch!

Try the nasi lemak.. Power . sambal cili sedapppp

formattedAddress: Lao Zhong Zhong Eating House (29 Tai Thong Crescent)

tips.text: Heard the lao zhong zhong wu xiang is nice.. Will come again to eat their wu xiang the next trip... ;)) great fishball noodle..
the duck rice not very fantastic.. Both rice n duck kinda tasteless... Not a bad thing i guess less msg added
Must try Gobi Manchurian. Okay food, pay as you want, but really bad attitude problem with the staff. I would love to dine more and pay more, but their service attitude really bums me out.
